abstract: The Trump administration said Tuesday that it is waiving federal contracting laws to speed construction of a wall at the U.S.-Mexico border, moving the president closer to fulfilling a signature campaign promise in an election year but sparking criticism about potential for fraud, waste and abuse.
snippet: The Trump administration said Tuesday that it is waiving federal contracting laws to speed construction of a wall at the U.S.-Mexico border, moving the president closer to fulfilling a signature campaign promise in an election year but sparking cr...
lead_paragraph: SAN DIEGO — The Trump administration said Tuesday that it is waiving federal contracting laws to speed construction of a wall at the U.S.-Mexico border, moving the president closer to fulfilling a signature campaign promise in an election year but sparking criticism about potential for fraud, waste and abuse.
headline_main: Homeland Security Waives Contracting Laws for Border Wall
headline_print_headline: Homeland Security Waives Contracting Laws for Border Wall

headline_main: On Politics: Bloomberg’s in the Debate

abstract: When Michael Bloomberg steps onto the Democratic debate stage for the first time on Wednesday, he will be ready to dismiss rivals like Joe Biden, who as vice president made "speeches that somebody writes for him," and Pete Buttigieg, "mayor of a town."
snippet: When Michael Bloomberg steps onto the Democratic debate stage for the first time on Wednesday, he will be ready to dismiss rivals like Joe Biden, who as vice president made "speeches that somebody writes for him," and Pete Buttigieg, "mayor of a t...
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — When Michael Bloomberg steps onto the Democratic debate stage for the first time on Wednesday, he will be ready to dismiss rivals like Joe Biden, who as vice president made "speeches that somebody writes for him," and Pete Buttigieg, "mayor of a town."
headline_main: Bloomberg Has Barbs at the Ready for His First 2020 Debate

abstract: The presidential candidate’s proposals for changing how the financial industry is regulated wouldn’t be out of place for his more left-leaning rivals.

abstract: At least six Democratic presidential contenders will meet in a pivotal debate in Nevada on Wednesday, three days before the state's voters make their picks in an unsettled and tight nominating race for the White House.
snippet: At least six Democratic presidential contenders will meet in a pivotal debate in Nevada on Wednesday, three days before the state's voters make their picks in an unsettled and tight nominating race for the White House.
lead_paragraph: (Reuters) - At least six Democratic presidential contenders will meet in a pivotal debate in Nevada on Wednesday, three days before the state's voters make their picks in an unsettled and tight nominating race for the White House.
headline_main: Democratic White House Candidates Face High-Pressure Nevada Debate
headline_print_headline: Democratic White House Candidates Face High-Pressure Nevada Debate

abstract: Former New York Mayor Michael Bloomberg on Tuesday qualified for this week's Democratic presidential debate in Nevada, putting him on the same stage as his rivals for the first time in the race for the party's nomination.
snippet: Former New York Mayor Michael Bloomberg on Tuesday qualified for this week's Democratic presidential debate in Nevada, putting him on the same stage as his rivals for the first time in the race for the party's nomination.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Former New York Mayor Michael Bloomberg on Tuesday qualified for this week's Democratic presidential debate in Nevada, putting him on the same stage as his rivals for the first time in the race for the party's nomination.
headline_main: Bloomberg Qualifies for Next Debate After Poll Boost
headline_print_headline: Bloomberg Qualifies for Next Debate After Poll Boost

abstract: For Mike Bloomberg, the one-way conversation with Democratic voters is about to end.
snippet: For Mike Bloomberg, the one-way conversation with Democratic voters is about to end.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — For Mike Bloomberg, the one-way conversation with Democratic voters is about to end.
headline_main: Bloomberg to Go Face to Face Against Rivals After Ad Blitz
headline_print_headline: Bloomberg to Go Face to Face Against Rivals After Ad Blitz

abstract: After garnering 19 percent support in a national poll, the billionaire will be on the debate stage, where he is certain to be a target of onstage criticism.
snippet: After garnering 19 percent support in a national poll, the billionaire will be on the debate stage, where he is certain to be a target of onstage criticism.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Former Mayor Michael R. Bloomberg of New York has qualified for the next two Democratic debates, including one on Wednesday in Las Vegas. It will be his first appearance onstage alongside his presidential rivals.

abstract: Ms. Warren’s campaign and her allies, convinced her message is being ignored, see a path forward — and they say writing her off would be a mistake.
snippet: Ms. Warren’s campaign and her allies, convinced her message is being ignored, see a path forward — and they say writing her off would be a mistake.
lead_paragraph: RENO, Nev. — A bad month for Senator Elizabeth Warren of Massachusetts keeps getting worse. She finished in a respectable third place in the Iowa caucuses, but a results-tallying meltdown muddled what could have been a good evening. New Hampshire was better at logistics but worse for her candidacy, considering she ended up closer to candidates who dropped out after the primary than those who finished on top.
